reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pretty, Fun and Convenient
reviews.reviewText: My sister has this lamp and my grandson was enthralled with its magical powers. Turning on and off with just a touch! He now has it in his bedroom and can easily control the brightness as well as turning it on and off. It’s a definite hit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Pretty, turn on by touching any portion
reviews.reviewText: This lamp is very pretty and the 3 light levels are great. However, I took off a star because it's misleading on how you turn the lamp on. The pictures show someone touching the base of the lamp to turn it on, but that's not correct. The lamp turns on when you touch any part of it (the beaded portion too). Not a big deal, but I specifically wanted a lamp where only the base turned it on, so my cats couldn't accidentally turn it on when they rub against it (which they are doing now, waking me up at 2am).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Cute bedside lamps
reviews.reviewText: Cute little bedside lamps for guest room. Touch on and off controls fun for my guests. Cellphone charger very handy for guests, but you need to purchase cords separately.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars DOES NOT WORK AFTER FEW DAYS
reviews.reviewText: Pros: the lamp is extremely bright on the lowest setting. Not my thing, but maybe some people would like that. But also - be aware that the wireless charging stand is millimeters away from where you tap it to turn it on, so reaching for your phone in the middle of the night is almost guaranteed to turn the brightest light possible on, and then you have to tap through EVEN BRIGHTER settings before it turns off. By then, you’re totally awake.The wireless charging totally stopped working after only a couple days. Then, the USB port stopped working too. I have contacted Amazon tech support who directed me to message the seller. I have twice now and still no response. I’m really frustrated that now I have to carry this lamp to the nearest UPS to return it - a huge hassle to find the time to do that, and all because this terrible scam of a product does not do as advertised at all.I don’t think I’ve ever written an Amazon review, but that’s how frustrated I am that this product ended up being so poorly designed, totally defective, and absolutely zero customer service from the seller.DO NOT BUY.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful but it didn’t last long
reviews.reviewText: I love this lamp but the charging ports only worked for three days, which was one of the reasons I bought it! I wanted to get rid of the need for more outlets.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2022
reviews.reviewText: First set arrived dented. Some dents you can’t see until the light is turned on so check carefully. These lights are better than advertised. You can touch the lamp ANYWHERE to turn it on, off, or adjust light level, not at just the base as the ad shows. They are a beautiful copper oil rubbed bronze color, more on the copper side. They have 3 dimming settings and give out a nice bright light at the brightest setting. It’s nice to be able to lean over and just touch the lamp to turn the light on in the middle of the night. The metal gets warm, but not hot to the touch. The “line” is at the back of the metal globe which looks nicer. The USB ports are an added bonus. They are elegant and perfect size. Love these lamps!
Su calidad corresponde a su precio y son de muy buena utilidad. Su encendido y apagado manual facilitan su uso...
